{{Egypt-geo-stub}}

'''Mount Taipingot''' lies at the southern end of [[Songsong]] Village on the [[Rota (island)|Rota]] in the [[Mariana Islands]]. It is connected to the main part of Rota by a [[tombolo]], on which is the southern part of Songsong village.  It is more commonly known as "Wedding Cake Mountain" because of its resemblance to a layered wedding cake. The areas in and around the mountain are conservation areas established to protect the native flora and fauna that thrive there.

